description: Product t2(q^d); d | 33, where t2(q) = theta2(q)/(2*q^(1/4)).
comments: The above function t2 simplifies to t2(z) = 1 + z^2 + z^6 + z^12 + ... = sum_{n>=0} z^(n(n+1)) = sum_{n>=0} z^A002378(n). But the sequence lists only the coefficients of even powers, i.e., with t2 replaced by t(z) = 1 + z + z^3 + z^6 + ..., cf. formula. - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 17 2014
formula: Coefficients of product_{d|33} t(x^d), with t(z) = sum_{n>=0} z^(n(n+1)/2) = sum_{n>=0} z^A00217(n). - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 17 2014
prog: (PARI) my(x='x+O('x^99), t(z)=sum(i=0, 10, z^((i+1)*i/2))); Vec(prod(i=1,#d=divisors(33), t(x^d[i]))) - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 17 2014
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
